## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Handler

**Only one file needs to change:** `common/chat.cpp` — in exactly two places.

---

### Step 1 — New handler function (after line 1517, before `namespace workaround`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    // Extract system message — prepended to first user message
    std::string system_content;
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        if (msg.value("role", "") == "system") {
            system_content = msg.value("content", "");
            break;
        }
    }

    std::string prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    if (inputs.add_bos) {
        prompt += tmpl.bos_token();
    }

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            continue;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                prompt += "[INST] " + (system_content.empty() ? "" : system_content + "\n") + content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

### Step 2 — Detection block (before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690)

```cpp
